    "body": "This PR introduces `T.CUDASourceCodeKernel`, which is another approach in TileLang to launch a GPU kernel. Instead of expressing the device-side body through TileLang DSL, users can provide CUDA source directly, either as inline code or via a source file path, and launch it from a TileLang PrimFunc.\r\n\r\n|  | T.CUDASourceCodeKernel(...) | with T.Kernel(...) |\r\n  |---|---|---|\r\n  | Programming model | Launches an external CUDA kernel directly | Builds the kernel body with the TileLang DSL |\r\n  | Kernel body source | Provided as CUDA source code or a source file path | Written inline inside the with block |\r\n  | Lowering path | Carries external source through IR attrs and injects it during CUDA codegen (**will ignore most TileLang TIR passes**) | Lowers the TileLang DSL body through the normal TileLang lowering pipeline |\r\n  | Best use case | Reusing hand-written CUDA kernels or externally generated CUDA code | Writing new kernels directly in TileLang |\r\n  | Flexibility for TileLang transformations | Limited by the fact that the device body is opaque external code | Higher, since the full kernel body is represented in TileLang IR |\r\n\r\nSome valuable points of this new API:\r\n- Users can embed CUDA code directly, and it is compiled **under the same environment** as a regular TileLang kernel. This means the CUDA code can also freely use utilities and headers from `tl_templates`.\r\n- Users can debug the TileLang generated kernel in source level, by first using `kernel..export_sources` and importing the CUDA through `T.CUDASourceCodeKernel`.\r\n- Comparing with exisiting embedding methods (`T.import_source` or `tilelang_callback_cuda_postproc`), this approach is more elegant, more maintainable, and better aligned with TileLang's standard lowering and codegen pipeline.\r\n-This API introduces a more explicit host-driven launch abstraction, which can be a precursor to HostDSL (an early building block for making TileLang a host-side control layer over both TileLang-generated kernels and externally authored device kernels.)\r\n\r\nImplementation Sketch:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"501\" height=\"640\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c0b11b2e-6766-4fe7-afcf-55445e159319\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\r\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\r\n\r\n* **New Features**\r\n  * Add CUDASourceCodeKernel to embed external CUDA source (inline or file) with optional explicit entry selection; external source can be emitted verbatim and mixed with regular kernels.\r\n  * Device ABI extraction can derive parameter order from external CUDA kernels for correct host/device wiring.\r\n\r\n* **Bug Fixes**\r\n  * Validate selected CUDA entry names and preserve user-specified device symbol names.\r\n  * Detect and report duplicate CUDA kernel symbols.\r\n\r\n* **Tests**\r\n  * New tests for inline/file kernels, explicit entry selection, ABI tracking, mixed kernels, and duplicate-entry rejection.\r\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
